It's the only way...

762
00:55:38,602 --> 00:55:40,576
...they'd let me stay.

763
00:55:40,842 --> 00:55:43,111
This is crazy.
You don't want to do this.

764
00:55:43,337 --> 00:55:45,312
Put it, put it down.

765
00:55:53,736 --> 00:55:55,165
Take it easy.

766
00:55:55,816 --> 00:55:57,310
You'll be all right.

767
00:55:58,312 --> 00:55:59,839
Him? What about me?

768
00:56:00,040 --> 00:56:02,342
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!

769
00:56:02,536 --> 00:56:04,358
You've had worse from shaving.

770
00:56:04,551 --> 00:56:06,558
What did you do to set him off?

771
00:56:06,760 --> 00:56:08,898
Nothing.
I come in here to say farewell.

772
00:56:09,479 --> 00:56:12,032
Ain't you heard?
His parole's come through.

773
00:56:14,279 --> 00:56:16,962
I just don't understand
what happened in there.

774
00:56:17,159 --> 00:56:19,842
Old man's crazy as a rat
in a tin shithouse.

775
00:56:20,038 --> 00:56:21,860
That's enough out of you.

776
00:56:22,054 --> 00:56:24,672
- Heard he had you shitting your pants.
- Fuck you.

777
00:56:24,934 --> 00:56:26,079
Knock it off.

778
00:56:27,014 --> 00:56:28,388
Brooks ain't no bug.

779
00:56:32,070 --> 00:56:33,760
He's just institutionalized.

780
00:56:35,077 --> 00:56:36,931
"Institutionalized," my ass.

781
00:56:37,125 --> 00:56:40,954
The man's been in here 50 years,
Heywood, 50 years!

782
00:56:41,157 --> 00:56:42,815
This is all he knows.

783
00:56:43,012 --> 00:56:45,216
In here, he's an important man...

784
00:56:45,412 --> 00:56:46,459
...an educated man.

785
00:56:47,235 --> 00:56:49,090
Outside, he's nothing.

786
00:56:49,923 --> 00:56:53,272
Just a used-up con
with arthritis in both hands.

787
00:56:53,475 --> 00:56:56,345
Probably couldn't get a library card
if he tried.

788
00:56:56,611 --> 00:56:58,269
You know what I'm trying to say?

789
00:56:58,531 --> 00:57:01,313
I do believe
you're talking out of your ass.

790
00:57:02,531 --> 00:57:04,669
You believe whatever you want.

791
00:57:05,250 --> 00:57:07,552
But I tell you these walls are funny.

792
00:57:09,090 --> 00:57:10,683
First you hate them.

793
00:57:12,449 --> 00:57:14,271
Then you get used to them.

794
00:57:16,129 --> 00:57:18,038
Enough time passes...

795
00:57:18,689 --> 00:57:20,599
...you get so you depend on them.

796
00:57:21,569 --> 00:57:23,674
That's "institutionalized."

797
00:57:23,872 --> 00:57:25,116
Shit.

798
00:57:25,313 --> 00:57:27,963
- I could never get like that.
- Oh, yeah?

799
00:57:28,801 --> 00:57:31,189
Wait till you've been here
as long as Brooks.

800
00:57:31,424 --> 00:57:32,918
Goddamn right.

801
00:57:35,391 --> 00:57:37,246
They send you here for life...

802
00:57:37,888 --> 00:57:40,124
...that's exactly what they take.

803
00:57:41,792 --> 00:57:43,701
Part that counts, anyway.

804
00:57:51,006 --> 00:57:53,821
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

805
00:57:54,942 --> 00:57:56,535
You go on now.

806
00:57:57,726 --> 00:57:59,154
You're free.

807
00:58:00,382 --> 00:58:01,876
You're free.

808
00:58:20,124 --> 00:58:21,717
Good luck, Brooksie.

809
00:58:58,136 --> 00:58:59,565
Dear fellas:

810
00:58:59,833 --> 00:59:03,858
I can't believe how fast things move
on the outside.

811
00:59:05,112 --> 00:59:07,664
Watch it, old-timer!
Want to get killed?

812
00:59:08,855 --> 00:59:12,204
I saw an automobile once
when I was a kid...

813
00:59:12,824 --> 00:59:15,158
...but now they're everywhere.

814
00:59:18,679 --> 00:59:22,803
The world went and got itself
in a big damn hurry.

815
00:59:37,973 --> 00:59:41,585
The parole board
got me into this halfway house...

816
00:59:41,877 --> 00:59:43,470
...called "The Brewer"...

817
00:59:43,668 --> 00:59:44,781
...and a job...

818
00:59:44,980 --> 00:59:47,827
...bagging groceries at the Food-Way.

819
00:59:49,300 --> 00:59:51,635
It's hard work and I try to keep up...

820
00:59:51,828 --> 00:59:54,097
...but my hands hurt most of the time.

821
00:59:54,388 --> 00:59:56,275
Make sure your man double-bags.

822
00:59:56,468 --> 00:59:58,410
Last time, the bottom near came out.

823
00:59:59,060 --> 01:00:01,874
Make sure you double-bag
like the lady says. Understand?

824
01:00:02,067 --> 01:00:03,376
Yes, sir. Surely will.

825
01:00:03,571 --> 01:00:06,953
I don't think the store manager
likes me very much.

826
01:00:09,842 --> 01:00:13,966
Sometimes after work,
I go to the park and feed the birds.

827
01:00:14,386 --> 01:00:15,815
I keep thinking...

828
01:00:16,050 --> 01:00:19,246
...Jake might just show up
and say hello.

829
01:00:19,826 --> 01:00:21,735
But he never does.

830
01:00:22,898 --> 01:00:27,567
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay
and making new friends.

831
01:00:31,025 --> 01:00:33,643
I have trouble sleeping at night.

832
01:00:33,936 --> 01:00:37,067
I have bad dreams like I'm falling.

833
01:00:37,328 --> 01:00:39,466
I wake up scared.

834
01:00:39,664 --> 01:00:43,722
Sometimes it takes me a while
to remember where I am.

835
01:00:45,167 --> 01:00:49,869
Maybe I should get a gun and rob
the Food-Way so they'd send me home.

836
01:00:50,159 --> 01:00:54,315
I could shoot the manager while
I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.

837
01:00:55,918 --> 01:00:59,747
I guess I'm too old
for that sort of nonsense anymore.

838
01:00:59,982 --> 01:01:01,640
I don't like it here.

839
01:01:01,838 --> 01:01:05,667
I'm tired of being afraid all the time.
I've decided...

840
01:01:06,477 --> 01:01:08,070
...not to stay.

841
01:01:18,540 --> 01:01:20,995
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...

842
01:01:21,196 --> 01:01:24,545
...not for an old crook like me.

843
01:02:24,455 --> 01:02:28,546
"l doubt they'll kick up any fuss,
not for an old crook like me.

844
01:02:29,542 --> 01:02:33,219
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry
I put a knife to his throat.

845
01:02:33,414 --> 01:02:35,650
No hard feelings. Brooks."

846
01:02:45,701 --> 01:02:47,588
He should have died in here.

847
01:02:52,901 --> 01:02:54,242
What the fuck have you done?

848
01:02:54,436 --> 01:02:56,989
It's a goddamn mess,
I'll tell you that.

849
01:03:02,307 --> 01:03:05,885
- What's all this?
- You tell me. They're addressed to you.

850
01:03:07,107 --> 01:03:08,383
Take it.

851
01:03:16,578 --> 01:03:18,007
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:

852
01:03:19,106 --> 01:03:20,993
In response to your inquiries...

853
01:03:21,186 --> 01:03:25,277
...the state has allocated the enclosed
funds for your library project."

854
01:03:26,017 --> 01:03:27,773
This is $200.

855
01:03:27,970 --> 01:03:31,799
"In addition, the library district
has generously responded...

856
01:03:32,001 --> 01:03:34,456
...with a donation of used books
and sundries.

857
01:03:34,657 --> 01:03:38,617
We trust this will fill your needs.
We now consider the matter closed.

858
01:03:38,817 --> 01:03:40,540
Please stop sending us letters."

859
01:03:40,768 --> 01:03:43,321
Clear all this out
before the warden gets back.

860
01:03:43,552 --> 01:03:44,664
Yes, sir.

861
01:03:48,768 --> 01:03:49,880
Good for you, Andy.

862
01:03:52,735 --> 01:03:53,815
Wow!

863
01:03:54,975 --> 01:03:56,830
It only took six years.

864
01:03:58,334 --> 01:04:00,952
From now on, I'll write two
letters a week instead of one.

865
01:04:01,151 --> 01:04:04,347
I believe you're crazy enough.
Get this stuff out...

866
01:04:04,606 --> 01:04:05,402
...like he said.

867
01:04:05,598 --> 01:04:06,940
I've got to pinch a loaf.

868
01:04:07,134 --> 01:04:08,540
When I come back...

869
01:04:08,734 --> 01:04:10,425
...this is all gone, all right?

870
01:04:57,178 --> 01:04:58,519
Do you hear that?

871
01:06:04,436 --> 01:06:05,549
Dufresne!

872
01:06:07,987 --> 01:06:09,449
Andy, let me out!

873
01:06:16,051 --> 01:06:20,786
I have no idea to this day what those
two Italian ladies were singing about.

874
01:06:21,074 --> 01:06:23,213
Truth is, I don't want to know.

875
01:06:23,410 --> 01:06:25,799
Some things are best left unsaid.

876
01:06:29,234 --> 01:06:31,852
I like to think it was something
so beautiful...

877
01:06:32,050 --> 01:06:34,089
...it can't be expressed in words...

878
01:06:34,290 --> 01:06:37,072
...and makes your heart ache
because of it.

879
01:06:38,673 --> 01:06:41,062
I tell you, those voices soared...

880
01:06:41,328 --> 01:06:45,452
...higher and farther than anybody
in a gray place dares to dream.

881
01:06:45,649 --> 01:06:48,877
It was like a beautiful bird
flapped into our drab cage...

882
01:06:49,072 --> 01:06:51,723
...and made those walls dissolve away.

883
01:06:52,144 --> 01:06:54,249
And for the briefest of moments...

884
01:06:54,448 --> 01:06:57,317
...every last man at Shawshank
felt free.

885
01:06:59,791 --> 01:07:02,344
It pissed the warden off
something awful.

886
01:07:03,598 --> 01:07:04,547
Open the door.

887
01:07:07,342 --> 01:07:09,033
Open it up!

888
01:07:10,286 --> 01:07:12,904
Dufresne, open this door!

889
01:07:14,190 --> 01:07:15,335
Turn that off!

890
01:07:22,125 --> 01:07:24,460
I am warning you. Turn that off!

891
01:07:41,484 --> 01:07:42,945
You're mine now.

892
01:07:50,091 --> 01:07:53,189
Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

893
01:07:53,387 --> 01:07:54,913
On your feet.

894
01:07:56,042 --> 01:07:58,343
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

895
01:08:00,042 --> 01:08:03,554
You couldn't play something good, huh?
Like Hank Williams?

896
01:08:03,881 --> 01:08:06,565
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

897
01:08:06,761 --> 01:08:09,761
- Was it worth two weeks?
- Easiest time I ever did.

898
01:08:09,961 --> 01:08:13,987
- No such thing as easy time in the hole.
- A week in the hole is like a year.

899
01:08:14,184 --> 01:08:17,348
- Damn straight.
- I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

900
01:08:17,545 --> 01:08:20,392
So they let you tote
that record player down there, huh?

901
01:08:22,728 --> 01:08:24,037
It was in here.

902
01:08:24,839 --> 01:08:26,017
In here.

903
01:08:27,111 --> 01:08:29,118
That's the beauty of music. They...

904
01:08:29,320 --> 01:08:31,556
...can't get that from you.

905
01:08:34,951 --> 01:08:37,220
Haven't you ever felt
that way about music?

906
01:08:38,950 --> 01:08:41,950
Well, I played a mean harmonica
as a younger man.

907
01:08:42,950 --> 01:08:44,576
Lost interest in it, though.

908
01:08:44,774 --> 01:08:46,301
Didn't make much sense in here.

909
01:08:46,630 --> 01:08:48,539
Here's where it makes the most sense.

910
01:08:49,062 --> 01:08:51,036
You need it so you don't forget.

911
01:08:51,590 --> 01:08:52,735
Forget?

912
01:08:53,093 --> 01:08:56,060
Forget that there are...

913
01:08:56,262 --> 01:08:57,636
...places...

914
01:08:58,117 --> 01:09:01,794
...in the world
that aren't made out of stone.

915
01:09:02,757 --> 01:09:04,185
There's something...

916
01:09:04,516 --> 01:09:05,858
...inside...

917
01:09:06,116 --> 01:09:08,003
...that they can't get to...

918
01:09:08,196 --> 01:09:09,505
...that they can't touch.

919
01:09:10,020 --> 01:09:11,394
That's yours.

920
01:09:12,868 --> 01:09:14,395
What are you talking about?

921
01:09:15,396 --> 01:09:16,573
Hope.

922
01:09:17,603 --> 01:09:18,880
Hope.

923
01:09:20,739 --> 01:09:22,648
Let me tell you something, my friend.

924
01:09:23,427 --> 01:09:25,631
Hope is a dangerous thing.

925
01:09:26,755 --> 01:09:28,991
Hope can drive a man insane.

926
01:09:29,699 --> 01:09:31,738
It's got no use on the inside.

927
01:09:31,938 --> 01:09:34,043
You'd better get used to that idea.

928
01:09:36,450 --> 01:09:37,878
Like Brooks did?

929
01:10:02,207 --> 01:10:03,156
Sit down.

930
01:10:08,287 --> 01:10:11,451
Says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

931
01:10:12,575 --> 01:10:14,549
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

932
01:10:14,750 --> 01:10:15,928
Oh, yes, sir.

933
01:10:17,150 --> 01:10:18,426
Without a doubt.

934
01:10:19,550 --> 01:10:21,852
I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

935
01:10:23,773 --> 01:10:25,628
No danger to society here.

936
01:10:26,141 --> 01:10:27,602
God's honest truth.

937
01:10:30,077 --> 01:10:32,085
Absolutely rehabilitated.

938
01:10:41,675 --> 01:10:42,951
Thirty years.

939
01:10:44,844 --> 01:10:46,666
Jesus, when you say it like that...

940
01:10:47,499 --> 01:10:49,222
You wonder where it went.

941
01:10:51,563 --> 01:10:53,635
I wonder where 10 years went.

942
01:10:58,410 --> 01:10:59,392
Here.

943
01:10:59,818 --> 01:11:02,436
A little parole rejection present.

944
01:11:03,657 --> 01:11:05,283
Go ahead and open it.

945
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:08,287
Went through one of your competitors.

946
01:11:08,490 --> 01:11:11,489
I hope you don't mind.
I wanted it to be a surprise.

947
01:11:21,128 --> 01:11:22,556
It's very pretty.

948
01:11:24,200 --> 01:11:25,345
Thank you.

949
01:11:27,815 --> 01:11:29,222
You going to play it?

950
01:11:33,607 --> 01:11:34,817
No.

951
01:11:38,279 --> 01:11:39,620
Not right now.

952
01:11:56,581 --> 01:11:57,628
Roll in!

953
01:12:32,354 --> 01:12:33,532
Lights out!

954
01:13:06,719 --> 01:13:08,758
Andy was as good as his word.

955
01:13:09,119 --> 01:13:11,769
He wrote two letters a week
instead of one.

956
01:13:13,758 --> 01:13:17,686
In 1959, the state senate
finally clued in to the fact...

957
01:13:17,918 --> 01:13:20,918
...they couldn't buy him off
with just a $200 check.

958
01:13:21,117 --> 01:13:25,241
Appropriations Committee
voted an annual payment of $500...

959
01:13:25,437 --> 01:13:27,259
...just to shut him up.

960
01:13:27,453 --> 01:13:30,322
And you'd be amazed how far
Andy could stretch it.

961
01:13:30,525 --> 01:13:33,339
He made deals with book clubs,
charity groups.

962
01:13:33,533 --> 01:13:36,184
He bought remaindered books
by the pound...

963
01:13:36,669 --> 01:13:38,130
Treasure Island.

964
01:13:38,652 --> 01:13:39,928
Robert Louis--

965
01:13:40,124 --> 01:13:41,106
Stevenson.

966
01:13:41,308 --> 01:13:42,617
Fiction, adventure.

967
01:13:45,084 --> 01:13:46,066
What's next?

968
01:13:46,268 --> 01:13:49,202
I got here Auto Repair...

969
01:13:49,915 --> 01:13:51,027
...and Soap Carving.

970
01:13:51,227 --> 01:13:54,325
Trade skills and hobbies.
Under "Educational," behind you.

971
01:13:54,523 --> 01:13:56,311
Count of Monte Crisco.

972
01:13:56,763 --> 01:13:58,966
That's "Cristo," you dumb shit.

973
01:14:00,026 --> 01:14:00,974
By Alexandree...

974
01:14:01,434 --> 01:14:02,644
...Dum-ass.

975
01:14:02,970 --> 01:14:03,952
Dumb ass.

976
01:14:06,170 --> 01:14:07,185
Dumb ass?

977
01:14:09,977 --> 01:14:11,864
Dumas. Know what that's about?

978
01:14:14,041 --> 01:14:15,928
You'd like it.
It's about a prison break.

979
01:14:16,121 --> 01:14:19,863
We ought to file that
under "Educational" too, oughtn't we?

980
01:14:20,696 --> 01:14:24,624
The rest of us did our best
to pitch in when and where we could.

981
01:14:25,176 --> 01:14:26,866
By the year Kennedy was shot...

982
01:14:27,096 --> 01:14:31,405
...Andy had transformed a storage room
smelling of turpentine...

983
01:14:31,703 --> 01:14:34,670
...into the best prison library
in New England...

984
01:14:35,351 --> 01:14:38,166
...complete with a fine selection
of Hank Williams.

985
01:14:45,238 --> 01:14:47,093
That was also when Warden Norton...

986
01:14:47,286 --> 01:14:50,101
...instituted his famous
"Inside Out" program.

987
01:14:50,550 --> 01:14:52,524
You may remember reading about it.

988
01:14:52,758 --> 01:14:55,725
It made the papers
and got his picture in Look magazine.

989
01:14:55,926 --> 01:14:57,169
It's no free ride...

990
01:14:57,365 --> 01:15:00,463
..but rather a genuine
progressive advance...

991
01:15:00,661 --> 01:15:03,050
...in corrections and rehabilitation.

992
01:15:03,381 --> 01:15:05,802
Our inmates, properly supervised...

993
01:15:06,004 --> 01:15:08,524
...will be put to work
outside these walls...

994
01:15:08,725 --> 01:15:12,140
...performing all manner
of public service.

995
01:15:12,404 --> 01:15:14,543
These men can learn the value...

996
01:15:14,740 --> 01:15:18,384
...of an honest day's labor and
provide a service to the community...

997
01:15:18,579 --> 01:15:23,085
...at a bare minimum of expense
to Mr. and Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.

998
01:15:23,507 --> 01:15:25,744
Of course he didn't tell the press...

999
01:15:25,939 --> 01:15:29,255
...that "bare minimum of expense"
is a fairly loose term.

1000
01:15:29,459 --> 01:15:32,360
There are 100 different ways
to skim off the top.

1001
01:15:32,563 --> 01:15:34,951
Men, materials, you name it.

1002
01:15:35,282 --> 01:15:38,064
And oh, my Lord,
how the money rolled in!

1003
01:15:38,258 --> 01:15:40,679
At this rate,
you'll put me out of business.

1004
01:15:40,882 --> 01:15:45,137
With this pool of slave labor,
you can underbid any contractor in town.

1005
01:15:45,681 --> 01:15:48,528
We're providing
a valuable community service.

1006
01:15:48,721 --> 01:15:52,234
That's fine for the papers,
but I've got a family to feed.

1007
01:15:54,801 --> 01:15:56,262
We go back a long way.

1008
01:15:57,521 --> 01:16:02,255
I need this highway contract. I don't
get it and I go under. That's a fact.

1009
01:16:03,120 --> 01:16:04,843
You have some of this fine pie...

1010
01:16:05,071 --> 01:16:08,268
...my missus made for you.
You think about that.

1011
01:16:16,207 --> 01:16:18,792
I wouldn't worry too much
about this contract.

1012
01:16:19,022 --> 01:16:21,957
I already got my boys
committed elsewhere.

1013
01:16:23,854 --> 01:16:26,788
You be sure and thank Maisie
for this fine pie.

1014
01:16:27,853 --> 01:16:29,926
And behind every shady deal...

1015
01:16:30,254 --> 01:16:32,774
...behind every dollar earned...

1016
01:16:33,038 --> 01:16:35,972
