What you got?

1262
01:30:30,821 --> 01:30:32,097
Board of Education.

1263
01:30:32,293 --> 01:30:33,755
That son of a bitch mailed it.

1264
01:30:33,957 --> 01:30:37,753
You going to open it or stand there
with your thumb up your butt?

1265
01:30:37,957 --> 01:30:40,029
Thumb up my butt sounds better.

1266
01:30:40,516 --> 01:30:43,233
Skeets, come on.
Give me that, you shithead.

1267
01:30:44,036 --> 01:30:45,313
Floyd, come on.

1268
01:30:50,531 --> 01:30:52,833
Will you throw that away, please?

1269
01:30:58,211 --> 01:30:59,869
Well, shit.

1270
01:31:12,033 --> 01:31:14,716
The kid passed. C + average.

1271
01:31:14,913 --> 01:31:16,920
Thought you'd like to know.

1272
01:31:32,480 --> 01:31:33,887
Warden wants to talk.

1273
01:31:47,071 --> 01:31:48,085
Out here?

1274
01:31:48,287 --> 01:31:50,425
That's what the man said.

1275
01:32:05,885 --> 01:32:06,833
Warden?

1276
01:32:16,444 --> 01:32:20,338
I'm asking you to keep this conversation
just between us.

1277
01:32:21,788 --> 01:32:23,959
I feel awkward enough as it is.

1278
01:32:41,658 --> 01:32:43,632
We got a situation here.

1279
01:32:44,474 --> 01:32:46,481
I think you can appreciate that.

1280
01:32:46,681 --> 01:32:47,859
Yes, sir.

1281
01:32:48,121 --> 01:32:49,462
I sure can.

1282
01:32:49,721 --> 01:32:53,583
I tell you, son, this thing really
came along and knocked my wind out.

1283
01:32:55,000 --> 01:32:57,455
It's got me up nights.
That's the truth.

1284
01:32:59,640 --> 01:33:01,396
The right thing to do...

1285
01:33:03,000 --> 01:33:06,578
...sometimes it's hard to know
what that is.

1286
01:33:07,544 --> 01:33:08,918
Do you understand?

1287
01:33:11,127 --> 01:33:12,654
I need your help, son.

1288
01:33:14,039 --> 01:33:16,111
If I'm going to move on this...

1289
01:33:16,439 --> 01:33:19,472
...there can't be
the least little shred of doubt.

1290
01:33:20,183 --> 01:33:21,197
I have to know...

1291
01:33:21,399 --> 01:33:23,919
...if what you told Dufresne
was the truth.

1292
01:33:24,118 --> 01:33:25,198
Yes, sir.

1293
01:33:25,398 --> 01:33:26,576
Absolutely.

1294
01:33:27,062 --> 01:33:29,931
Would you be willing to swear
before a judge and jury...

1295
01:33:30,134 --> 01:33:32,043
...with your hand on the Good Book...

1296
01:33:32,245 --> 01:33:34,798
...and take an oath
before Almighty God himself?

1297
01:33:34,998 --> 01:33:36,721
Just give me that chance.

1298
01:33:40,820 --> 01:33:42,097
That's what I thought.

1299
01:34:27,248 --> 01:34:29,070
I'm sure by now you've heard.

1300
01:34:30,769 --> 01:34:31,751
Terrible thing.

1301
01:34:33,297 --> 01:34:34,703
A man that young...

1302
01:34:35,025 --> 01:34:37,512
...less than a year to go,
trying to escape.

1303
01:34:38,032 --> 01:34:40,421
Broke Captain Hadley's heart
to shoot him.

1304
01:34:41,136 --> 01:34:42,565
Truly, it did.

1305
01:34:45,455 --> 01:34:47,789
We just have to put it behind us.

1306
01:34:49,391 --> 01:34:50,568
Move on.

1307
01:34:52,110 --> 01:34:53,539
I'm done.

1308
01:34:54,798 --> 01:34:56,359
Everything stops.

1309
01:34:58,254 --> 01:35:00,491
Get someone else to run your scams.

1310
01:35:01,710 --> 01:35:03,465
Nothing stops.

1311
01:35:04,749 --> 01:35:05,862
Nothing.

1312
01:35:09,133 --> 01:35:12,100
Or you will do
the hardest time there is.

1313
01:35:12,493 --> 01:35:14,697
No more protection from the guards.

1314
01:35:14,925 --> 01:35:19,627
I'll pull you out of that 1-bunk Hilton
and cast you down with the sodomites.

1315
01:35:20,972 --> 01:35:23,306
You'll think you've been
fucked by a train.

1316
01:35:24,652 --> 01:35:26,081
And the library?

1317
01:35:26,732 --> 01:35:27,680
Gone.

1318
01:35:28,268 --> 01:35:30,723
Sealed off, brick by brick.

1319
01:35:31,179 --> 01:35:33,732
We'll have us a little
book barbecue in the yard.

1320
01:35:33,932 --> 01:35:35,971
They'll see the flames for miles.

1321
01:35:36,171 --> 01:35:38,887
We'll dance around it like wild Injuns.

1322
01:35:40,106 --> 01:35:42,975
You understand me? Catching my drift?

1323
01:35:46,570 --> 01:35:48,358
Or am I being obtuse?

1324
01:35:59,657 --> 01:36:02,177
Give him another month
to think about it.

1325
01:36:47,013 --> 01:36:49,947
My wife used to say
I'm a hard man to know.

1326
01:36:50,725 --> 01:36:52,481
Like a closed book.

1327
01:36:53,253 --> 01:36:55,195
Complained about it all the time.

1328
01:36:56,100 --> 01:36:57,594
She was beautiful.

1329
01:36:59,908 --> 01:37:01,369
God, I loved her.

1330
01:37:04,931 --> 01:37:07,069
I didn't know how
to show it, that's all.

1331
01:37:09,699 --> 01:37:11,292
I killed her, Red.

1332
01:37:13,091 --> 01:37:14,814
I didn't pull the trigger...

1333
01:37:16,194 --> 01:37:17,852
...but I drove her away.

1334
01:37:19,298 --> 01:37:21,883
That's why she died, because of me...

1335
01:37:22,082 --> 01:37:23,391
...the way I am.

1336
01:37:32,033 --> 01:37:33,789
That don't make you a murderer.

1337
01:37:37,024 --> 01:37:38,715
Bad husband, maybe.

1338
01:37:42,209 --> 01:37:45,340
Feel bad about it if you want,
but you didn't pull the trigger.

1339
01:37:45,536 --> 01:37:46,812
No, I didn't.

1340
01:37:47,200 --> 01:37:49,055
Somebody else did.

1341
01:37:50,240 --> 01:37:52,247
And I wound up in here.

1342
01:37:54,623 --> 01:37:56,150
Bad luck, I guess.

1343
01:38:01,151 --> 01:38:02,525
It floats around.

1344
01:38:03,519 --> 01:38:05,657
It's got to land on somebody.

1345
01:38:06,526 --> 01:38:08,348
It was my turn, that's all.

1346
01:38:09,022 --> 01:38:11,673
I was in the path of the tornado.

1347
01:38:17,373 --> 01:38:21,169
I just didn't expect the storm
would last as long as it has.

1348
01:38:25,341 --> 01:38:26,966
Think you'll ever get out of here?

1349
01:38:28,156 --> 01:38:29,138
Me?

1350
01:38:31,996 --> 01:38:32,944
Yeah.

1351
01:38:34,236 --> 01:38:36,440
One day, when I got
a long, white beard...

1352
01:38:36,635 --> 01:38:39,668
...and two or three marbles
rolling around upstairs.

1353
01:38:41,627 --> 01:38:43,187
I tell you where I'd go.

1354
01:38:44,603 --> 01:38:46,196
Zihuatanejo.

1355
01:38:47,034 --> 01:38:48,179
Say what?

1356
01:38:48,474 --> 01:38:50,230
Zihuatanejo.

1357
01:38:51,130 --> 01:38:52,723
It's in Mexico.

1358
01:38:54,042 --> 01:38:56,082
A little place on the Pacific Ocean.

1359
01:38:57,178 --> 01:38:59,861
You know what the Mexicans say
about the Pacific?

1360
01:39:01,593 --> 01:39:03,502
They say it has no memory.

1361
01:39:05,401 --> 01:39:07,954
That's where I want to live
the rest of my life.

1362
01:39:09,528 --> 01:39:11,917
A warm place with no memory.

1363
01:39:15,032 --> 01:39:16,886
Open up a little hotel...

1364
01:39:18,520 --> 01:39:19,948
...right on the beach.

1365
01:39:20,535 --> 01:39:22,640
Buy some worthless old boat...

1366
01:39:23,159 --> 01:39:24,719
...and fix it up new.

1367
01:39:27,351 --> 01:39:28,528
Take my guests out...

1368
01:39:29,335 --> 01:39:30,644
...charter fishing.

1369
01:39:34,326 --> 01:39:35,984
Zihuatanejo.

1370
01:39:39,382 --> 01:39:43,091
In a place like that, I could use
a man that knows how to get things.

1371
01:39:49,365 --> 01:39:52,082
I don't think I could make it
on the outside.

1372
01:39:58,484 --> 01:40:00,459
I been in here most of my life.

1373
01:40:01,844 --> 01:40:03,535
I'm an institutional man now.

1374
01:40:04,404 --> 01:40:06,062
Just like Brooks was.

1375
01:40:07,475 --> 01:40:09,101
You underestimate yourself.

1376
01:40:09,651 --> 01:40:11,178
I don't think so.

1377
01:40:14,867 --> 01:40:18,642
In here I'm the guy who can get things
for you, sure, but...

1378
01:40:19,379 --> 01:40:21,800
...outside all you need
is the Yellow Pages.

1379
01:40:22,003 --> 01:40:24,141
Hell, I wouldn't know
where to begin.

1380
01:40:26,194 --> 01:40:27,754
Pacific Ocean?

1381
01:40:28,146 --> 01:40:29,323
Shit.

1382
01:40:29,682 --> 01:40:31,787
Scare me to death,
something that big.

1383
01:40:31,985 --> 01:40:33,229
Not me.

1384
01:40:34,386 --> 01:40:37,036
I didn't shoot my wife,
and I didn't shoot her lover.

1385
01:40:38,705 --> 01:40:41,803
Whatever mistakes I made,
I've paid for them and then some.

1386
01:40:42,801 --> 01:40:44,229
That hotel, that boat...

1387
01:40:45,936 --> 01:40:48,075
I don't think that's too much to ask.

1388
01:40:52,783 --> 01:40:55,117
You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.

1389
01:40:55,311 --> 01:40:57,253
This is just shitty pipe dreams.

1390
01:40:57,679 --> 01:41:00,046
Mexico is way down there
and you're in here...

1391
01:41:00,239 --> 01:41:01,733
...and that's the way it is.

1392
01:41:02,063 --> 01:41:04,780
Yeah, right.
That's the way it is.

1393
01:41:06,222 --> 01:41:08,524
It's down there and I'm in here.

1394
01:41:10,990 --> 01:41:13,608
I guess it comes down
to a simple choice.

1395
01:41:16,398 --> 01:41:17,827
Get busy living...

1396
01:41:19,150 --> 01:41:21,092
...or get busy dying.

1397
01:41:32,716 --> 01:41:35,334
If you ever get out of here,
do me a favor.

1398
01:41:35,532 --> 01:41:37,703
Sure, Andy. Anything.

1399
01:41:39,500 --> 01:41:43,209
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.
You know where Buxton is?

1400
01:41:44,619 --> 01:41:47,618
- A lot of hayfields up there.
- One in particular.

1401
01:41:47,819 --> 01:41:51,593
It's got a long rock wall
with a big oak tree at the north end.

1402
01:41:51,787 --> 01:41:54,536
It's like something
out of a Robert Frost poem.

1403
01:41:55,434 --> 01:41:57,823
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.

1404
01:41:59,178 --> 01:42:01,185
We went there for a picnic...

1405
01:42:01,578 --> 01:42:03,585
...and made love under that oak...

1406
01:42:04,233 --> 01:42:06,372
...and I asked and she said yes.

1407
01:42:10,217 --> 01:42:11,973
Promise me, Red.

1408
01:42:12,777 --> 01:42:14,337
If you ever get out...

1409
01:42:14,536 --> 01:42:15,965
...find that spot.

1410
01:42:17,097 --> 01:42:21,733
At the base of that wall, there's a rock
that has no earthly business in Maine.

1411
01:42:22,824 --> 01:42:25,726
Piece of black, volcanic glass.

1412
01:42:28,296 --> 01:42:30,848
Something's buried under it
I want you to have.

1413
01:42:31,592 --> 01:42:32,769
What, Andy?

1414
01:42:33,191 --> 01:42:34,849
What's buried under there?

1415
01:42:36,391 --> 01:42:38,180
You'll have to pry it up...

1416
01:42:38,374 --> 01:42:39,584
...to see.

1417
01:42:45,222 --> 01:42:47,109
No, I'm telling you. The guy is...

1418
01:42:47,750 --> 01:42:49,408
He's talking funny.

1419
01:42:50,470 --> 01:42:52,095
I'm really worried about him.

1420
01:42:52,485 --> 01:42:53,859
Let's keep an eye on him.

1421
01:42:54,053 --> 01:42:57,184
That's fine during the day,
but at night he's all alone.

1422
01:42:58,565 --> 01:42:59,645
Oh, Lord.

1423
01:43:00,933 --> 01:43:01,729
What?

1424
01:43:03,173 --> 01:43:05,823
Andy come down
to the loading dock today.

1425
01:43:06,020 --> 01:43:08,027
He asked me for a length of rope.

1426
01:43:08,228 --> 01:43:09,024
Rope?

1427
01:43:09,220 --> 01:43:10,813
Six feet long.

1428
01:43:11,044 --> 01:43:12,353
And you gave it to him.

1429
01:43:13,187 --> 01:43:14,911
Sure. Why wouldn't l?

1430
01:43:15,107 --> 01:43:16,601
Jesus! Heywood.

1431
01:43:17,187 --> 01:43:19,074
How was I supposed to know?

1432
01:43:19,267 --> 01:43:20,761
Remember Brooks Hatlen?

1433
01:43:22,691 --> 01:43:24,545
Andy would never do that.

1434
01:43:25,122 --> 01:43:26,137
Never.

1435
01:43:28,131 --> 01:43:29,407
I don't know.

1436
01:43:32,130 --> 01:43:34,071
Every man has his breaking point.

1437
01:43:36,321 --> 01:43:38,492
Lickety-split.
Want to get home.

1438
01:43:38,786 --> 01:43:40,476
Just about finished, sir.

1439
01:43:56,896 --> 01:43:58,456
Three deposits tonight.

1440
01:44:06,111 --> 01:44:07,933
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1441
01:44:08,127 --> 01:44:09,687
And shine my shoes.

1442
01:44:09,887 --> 01:44:12,701
- I want them looking like mirrors.
- Yes, sir.

1443
01:44:17,982 --> 01:44:19,389
It's good having you back.

1444
01:44:20,286 --> 01:44:22,074
Place wasn't the same without you.

1445
01:45:07,034 --> 01:45:08,048
Lights out!

1446
01:45:39,543 --> 01:45:41,964
I've had some long nights in stir.

1447
01:45:42,487 --> 01:45:45,039
Alone in the dark
with nothing but your thoughts...

1448
01:45:45,239 --> 01:45:47,792
...time can draw out like a blade.

1449
01:45:52,918 --> 01:45:55,787
That was the longest night of my life.

1450
01:46:10,996 --> 01:46:12,109
Give me a count!

1451
01:46:16,436 --> 01:46:19,152
Tier 3 south, clear!

1452
01:46:22,163 --> 01:46:25,197
Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!

1453
01:46:25,395 --> 01:46:26,410
Dufresne!

1454
01:46:26,930 --> 01:46:29,265
Come out. You're holding up the show!

1455
01:46:32,275 --> 01:46:35,536
Don't make me come down
or I'll thump your skull for you!

1456
01:46:42,801 --> 01:46:46,478
Damn it, you're putting me behind!
I got a schedule to keep.

1457
01:46:46,674 --> 01:46:49,837
You'd better be sick or dead in there.
I shit you not!

1458
01:46:50,033 --> 01:46:51,309
You hear me?

1459
01:46:57,168 --> 01:46:59,175
Oh, my Holy God.

1460
01:47:15,471 --> 01:47:17,926
I want every man
on this cellblock questioned.

1461
01:47:18,351 --> 01:47:20,806
- Start with that friend of his.
- Who?

1462
01:47:23,278 --> 01:47:24,772
Open 237.

1463
01:47:28,142 --> 01:47:31,654
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"?
Don't say that to me.

1464
01:47:32,494 --> 01:47:33,770
Don't tell me that again.

1465
01:47:33,966 --> 01:47:34,947
But sir, he wasn't.

1466
01:47:35,181 --> 01:47:38,498
I can see that, Haig!
Think I'm blind?

1467
01:47:39,149 --> 01:47:40,490
Is that what you're saying?

1468
01:47:40,685 --> 01:47:43,238
- Am I blind, Haig?
- No, sir!

1469
01:47:44,108 --> 01:47:46,497
What about you. You blind?

1470
01:47:46,988 --> 01:47:49,443
- Tell me what this is.
- Last night's count.

1471
01:47:49,644 --> 01:47:52,807
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. Right there.

1472
01:47:53,004 --> 01:47:54,280
"Dufresne."

1473
01:47:55,883 --> 01:47:57,290
He was in his cell...

1474
01:47:57,516 --> 01:47:58,443
...at lights out.

1475
01:47:58,635 --> 01:48:00,806
Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.

1476
01:48:01,803 --> 01:48:03,363
I want him found.

1477
01:48:03,563 --> 01:48:06,879
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1478
01:48:07,115 --> 01:48:08,260
Yes, sir.

1479
01:48:09,226 --> 01:48:11,397
Let's go. Move your butts.

1480
01:48:14,666 --> 01:48:15,614
Stand.

1481
01:48:17,002 --> 01:48:18,016
Well?

1482
01:48:21,321 --> 01:48:22,269
Well, what?

1483
01:48:22,473 --> 01:48:25,790
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

1484
01:48:26,824 --> 01:48:28,253
He must have said something.

1485
01:48:28,968 --> 01:48:30,430
No, sir, Warden.

1486
01:48:30,792 --> 01:48:31,720
Not a word.

1487
01:48:33,480 --> 01:48:35,935
Lord, it's a miracle!

1488
01:48:36,519 --> 01:48:38,974
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1489
01:48:39,623 --> 01:48:40,736
Nothing left...

1490
01:48:41,543 --> 01:48:44,161
...but some damn rocks
on a windowsill.

1491
01:48:44,359 --> 01:48:46,977
And that cupcake on the wall.
Let's ask her.

1492
01:48:47,175 --> 01:48:48,866
Maybe she knows.

1493
01:48:49,095 --> 01:48:51,713
What say there, fuzzy-britches?
Feel like talking?

1494
01:48:53,094 --> 01:48:54,338
Guess not.

1495
01:48:54,886 --> 01:48:56,991
Why should she be any different?

1496
01:48:58,022 --> 01:48:59,615
This is a conspiracy.

1497
01:49:00,230 --> 01:49:01,985
That's what this is.

1498
01:49:02,566 --> 01:49:06,143
One big, damn conspiracy!

1499
01:49:06,405 --> 01:49:08,315
And everyone's in on it!

1500
01:49:08,933 --> 01:49:10,045
Including her!

1501
01:49:43,650 --> 01:49:45,276
In 1966...

1502
01:49:45,474 --> 01:49:47,776
...Andy Dufresne escaped...

1503
01:49:47,969 --> 01:49:49,463
...from Shawshank Prison.

1504
01:49:51,617 --> 01:49:54,072
All they found
was a muddy set of prison clothes...

1505
01:49:54,689 --> 01:49:56,150
...a bar of soap...

1506
01:49:56,353 --> 01:49:57,847
...and an old rock hammer...

1507
01:49:58,049 --> 01:50:00,416
...damn near worn down to the nub.

1508
01:50:04,736 --> 01:50:09,307
I had thought it'd take a man 600 years
to tunnel through the wall with it.

1509
01:50:09,920 --> 01:50:12,440
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

1510
01:50:29,982 --> 01:50:32,186
Oh, Andy loved geology.

1511
01:50:32,925 --> 01:50:35,959
I imagine it appealed to his
meticulous nature.

1512
01:50:36,350 --> 01:50:38,106
An ice age here...

1513
01:50:38,526 --> 01:50:40,914
...million years
of mountain building there.

1514
01:50:41,885 --> 01:50:44,602
Geology is the study
of pressure and time.

1515
01:50:45,404 --> 01:50:47,314
That's all it takes, really.

1516
01:50:48,028 --> 01:50:49,075
Pressure...

1517
01:50:49,693 --> 01:50:50,903
...and time.

1518
01:50:52,188 --> 01:50:54,162
That and a big goddamn poster.

1519
01:50:58,043 --> 01:50:58,937
Like I said...

1520
01:50:59,419 --> 01:51:03,249
...in prison, a man will do anything
to keep his mind occupied.

1521
01:51:05,947 --> 01:51:10,551
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting
his wall out into the exercise yard...

1522
01:51:11,066 --> 01:51:12,921
...a handful at a time.

1523
01:51:14,170 --> 01:51:16,145
I guess after Tommy was killed...

1524
01:51:16,346 --> 01:51:19,193
...Andy decided
he'd been here long enough.

1525
01:51:19,386 --> 01:51:21,841
Lickety-split.
I want to get home.

1526
01:51:22,553 --> 01:51:24,495
I'm just about finished, sir.

1527
01:51:45,079 --> 01:51:46,934
Three deposits tonight.

1528
01:51:53,943 --> 01:51:56,147
Andy did like he was told.

1529
01:51:56,342 --> 01:51:59,691
Buffed those shoes
to a high mirror-shine.

1530
01:52:03,222 --> 01:52:05,426
The guards simply didn't notice.

1531
01:52:05,718 --> 01:52:07,125
Neither did l.

1532
01:52:07,318 --> 01:52:08,779
I mean, seriously...

1533
01:52:08,981 --> 01:52:11,851
...how often do you really look
at a man's shoes?

1534
01:54:10,347 --> 01:54:13,380
Andy crawled to freedom
through 500 yards...

1535
01:54:13,611 --> 01:54:16,807
...of shit-smelling foulness
I can't even imagine.

1536
01:54:17,770 --> 01:54:20,007
Or maybe I just don't want to.

1537
01:54:24,234 --> 01:54:26,503
Five hundred yards.

1538
01:54:26,986 --> 01:54:29,920
That's the length
of five football fields.

1539
01:54:30,537 --> 01:54:32,992
Just shy of half a mile.

1540
01:55:25,956 --> 01:55:30,364
The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her secret...

1541
01:55:30,660 --> 01:55:33,377
...a man nobody ever
laid eyes on before...

1542
01:55:33,604 --> 01:55:36,091
...strolled into
the Maine National Bank.

1543
01:55:36,644 --> 01:55:39,677
Until that moment,
he didn't exist.

1544
01:55:40,227 --> 01:55:42,496
- Except on paper.
- May I help you?

1545
01:55:42,883 --> 01:55:44,737
He had all the proper ID...

1546
01:55:44,931 --> 01:55:48,476
...driver's license, birth certificate,
Social Security card...

1547
01:55:48,898 --> 01:55:51,320
And the signature
was a spot-on match.

1548
01:55:51,522 --> 01:55:54,489
I must say I'm sorry
to be losing your business.

1549
01:55:54,690 --> 01:55:56,349
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1550
01:55:57,121 --> 01:55:58,169
Thank you.

1551
01:55:58,818 --> 01:55:59,930
I'm sure I will.

1552
01:56:00,802 --> 01:56:03,998
Here's your cashier's check, sir.
Will there be anything else?

1553
01:56:04,194 --> 01:56:05,142
Please.

1554
01:56:05,697 --> 01:56:08,086
Would you add this
to your outgoing mail?

1555
01:56:08,577 --> 01:56:09,722
I'd be happy to.

1556
01:56:11,457 --> 01:56:12,733
Good day, sir.

1557
01:56:13,633 --> 01:56:17,888
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.

1558
01:56:18,336 --> 01:56:19,863
All told, he blew town...

1559
01:56:20,064 --> 01:56:24,700
...with better than $370,000
of Warden Norton's money.

1560
01:56:25,375 --> 01:56:28,026
Severance pay for 19 years.

1561
01:56:34,974 --> 01:56:37,079
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

1562
01:57:27,770 --> 01:57:30,584
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

1563
01:57:30,841 --> 01:57:35,096
If you give up this right, anything you
say can be held against you in court.

1564
01:57:35,513 --> 01:57:39,790
I wasn't there to see, but I hear
Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

1565
01:57:39,993 --> 01:57:41,422
...when they took him away.

1566
01:57:47,064 --> 01:57:50,326
Norton had no intention
of going that quietly.

1567
01:58:05,527 --> 01:58:06,323
Samuel Norton.

1568
01:58:07,095 --> 01:58:09,429
We have a warrant
for your arrest. Open up.

1569
01:58:13,974 --> 01:58:15,022
Open the door.

1570
01:58:15,542 --> 01:58:16,753
I'm not sure which key.

1571
01:58:26,485 --> 01:58:28,340
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1572
01:58:39,380 --> 01:58:42,696
I like to think the last thing
that went through his head...

1573
01:58:42,899 --> 01:58:44,426
...other than that bullet...

1574
01:58:44,628 --> 01:58:48,882
...was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

1575
01:58:51,283 --> 01:58:54,599
Not long after the warden
deprived us of his company...

1576
01:58:54,866 --> 01:58:56,841
...I got a postcard in the mail.

1577
01:58:58,258 --> 01:59:00,975
It was blank,
but the postmark said...

1578
01:59:01,171 --> 01:59:03,210
...Fort Hancock, Texas.

1579
01:59:03,730 --> 01:59:05,039
Fort Hancock...

1580
01:59:05,298 --> 01:59:06,956
...right on the border.

1581
01:59:07,345 --> 01:59:09,255
That's where Andy crossed.

1582
01:59:09,810 --> 01:59:13,770
When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down...

1583
01:59:14,097 --> 01:59:16,236
...it always makes me laugh.

1584
01:59:18,000 --> 01:59:19,494
Andy Dufresne...

1585
01:59:19,857 --> 01:59:21,799
...who crawled through
a river of shit...

1586
01:59:22,000 --> 01:59:24,302
...and came out clean
on the other side.

1587
01:59:25,104 --> 01:59:26,413
Andy Dufresne...

1588
01:59:27,184 --> 01:59:28,711
...headed for the Pacific.

1589
01:59:31,568 --> 01:59:33,640
Hadley's got him
by the throat, right?

1590
01:59:33,839 --> 01:59:37,483
He says, "l believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident."

1591
01:59:37,679 --> 01:59:40,428
Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.

1592
01:59:41,071 --> 01:59:42,696
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

1593
01:59:42,895 --> 01:59:45,742
"My friends could use
a couple of beers."

1594
01:59:46,062 --> 01:59:47,655
And he got it!

1595
01:59:48,846 --> 01:59:51,148
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

1596
01:59:51,406 --> 01:59:52,780
...Andy being gone.

1597
01:59:53,454 --> 01:59:57,414
I have to remind myself that
some birds aren't meant to be caged.

1598
01:59:57,869 --> 01:59:59,843
Their feathers are just too bright.

1599
02:00:01,485 --> 02:00:03,143
And when they fly away...

1600
02:00:03,565 --> 02:00:07,787
...the part of you that knows it was
a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

1601
02:00:08,813 --> 02:00:10,023
But still...

1602
02:00:10,476 --> 02:00:14,632
...the place you live in is that much
more drab and empty that they're gone.

1603
02:00:18,668 --> 02:00:20,937
I guess I just miss my friend.

1604
02:00:44,617 --> 02:00:45,511
Please sit down.

1605
02:00:51,112 --> 02:00:52,606
Ellis Boyd Redding...

1606
02:00:53,129 --> 02:00:56,260
...your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

1607
02:00:57,032 --> 02:00:59,072
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1608
02:01:00,872 --> 02:01:02,366
Rehabilitated?

1609
02:01:04,328 --> 02:01:06,150
Well, now, let me see.

1610
02:01:07,111 --> 02:01:09,348
I don't have any idea
what that means.

1611
02:01:11,367 --> 02:01:13,538
It means you're ready
to rejoin society--

1612
02:01:14,087 --> 02:01:16,323
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1613
02:01:18,406 --> 02:01:20,315
To me it's just a made-up word.

1614
02:01:21,606 --> 02:01:23,842
A politician's word so that...

1615
02:01:24,262 --> 02:01:27,644
...young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie...

1616
02:01:28,101 --> 02:01:29,628
...and have a job.

1617
02:01:31,526 --> 02:01:33,533
What do you really want to know?

1618
02:01:34,277 --> 02:01:36,164
Am I sorry for what I did?

1619
02:01:36,580 --> 02:01:37,693
Well, are you?

1620
02:01:39,524 --> 02:01:42,241
There's not a day goes by
I don't feel regret.

1621
02:01:43,556 --> 02:01:46,872
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

1622
02:01:50,212 --> 02:01:52,667
I look back on the way I was then...

1623
02:01:54,723 --> 02:01:55,835
...a young...

1624
02:01:56,899 --> 02:02:00,247
...stupid kid who committed
that terrible crime.

1625
02:02:03,139 --> 02:02:04,764
I want to talk to him.

1626
02:02:06,626 --> 02:02:08,993
I want to try
and talk some sense to him.

1627
02:02:09,698 --> 02:02:11,553
Tell him the way things are.

1628
02:02:13,569 --> 02:02:14,943
But I can't.

1629
02:02:17,057 --> 02:02:18,966
That kid's long gone...

1630
02:02:20,129 --> 02:02:22,779
...and this old man is all that's left.

1631
02:02:24,128 --> 02:02:25,535
I got to live with that.

1632
02:02:26,848 --> 02:02:28,473
Rehabilitated?

1633
02:02:28,832 --> 02:02:30,588
It's just a bullshit word.

1634
02:02:31,488 --> 02:02:36,060
So you go on and stamp your forms,
sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1635
02:02:37,248 --> 02:02:39,419
Because to tell you the truth...

1636
02:02:39,743 --> 02:02:41,652
...I don't give a shit.

1637
02:04:04,632 --> 02:04:05,974
Here you go, miss.

1638
02:04:08,792 --> 02:04:09,774
Restroom break?

1639
02:04:15,351 --> 02:04:19,693
You don't need to ask me every time
you need to go take a piss. Just go.

1640
02:04:32,214 --> 02:04:35,148
Forty years I've been asking
permission to piss.

1641
02:04:35,957 --> 02:04:38,827
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

1642
02:04:42,196 --> 02:04:44,269
There's a harsh truth to face.

1643
02:04:45,877 --> 02:04:48,659
No way I'm going to make it
on the outside.

1644
02:04:56,211 --> 02:04:59,757
All I do anymore is think of ways
to break my parole...

1645
02:05:00,532 --> 02:05:02,898
...so maybe they'd send me back.

1646
02:05:07,891 --> 02:05:10,225
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

1647
02:05:11,091 --> 02:05:12,684
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

1648
02:05:12,882 --> 02:05:14,737
Knew it all too well.

1649
02:05:16,274 --> 02:05:19,535
All I want is to be back
where things make sense.

1650
02:05:19,953 --> 02:05:22,571
Where I won't have to be afraid
all the time.

1651
02:05:24,497 --> 02:05:26,766
Only one thing stops me.

1652
02:05:28,145 --> 02:05:30,446
A promise I made to Andy.

1653
02:05:50,127 --> 02:05:51,207
There it is.

1654
02:06:01,390 --> 02:06:02,983
Much obliged, sir.

1655
02:09:33,307 --> 02:09:34,518
Dear Red:

1656
02:09:34,748 --> 02:09:37,114
If you're reading this,
you've gotten out...

1657
02:09:37,307 --> 02:09:41,201
...and if you've come this far,
maybe you'd come a bit further.

1658
02:09:41,467 --> 02:09:43,834
You remember the name
of the town, don't you?

1659
02:09:46,042 --> 02:09:47,471
Zihuatanejo.

1660
02:09:49,051 --> 02:09:52,498
I could use a good man
to help me get my project on wheels.

1661
02:09:52,986 --> 02:09:56,368
I'll keep an eye out for you,
and the chessboard ready.

1662
02:09:57,146 --> 02:09:58,488
Remember, Red...

1663
02:09:58,810 --> 02:10:00,817
...hope is a good thing...

1664
02:10:01,017 --> 02:10:02,927
...maybe the best of things.

1665
02:10:03,129 --> 02:10:05,201
And no good thing ever dies.

1666
02:10:05,721 --> 02:10:08,470
I will be hoping
that this letter finds you...

1667
02:10:08,665 --> 02:10:10,323
...and finds you well.

1668
02:10:10,808 --> 02:10:11,986
Your friend...

1669
02:10:12,184 --> 02:10:13,297
...Andy.

1670
02:10:45,750 --> 02:10:47,408
"Get busy living...

1671
02:10:47,606 --> 02:10:49,428
...or get busy dying. "

1672
02:10:52,021 --> 02:10:54,093
That's goddamn right.

1673
02:10:59,125 --> 02:11:01,164
For the second time in my life...

1674
02:11:01,396 --> 02:11:03,851
...I'm guilty of committing a crime.

1675
02:11:04,884 --> 02:11:06,739
Parole violation.

1676
02:11:07,379 --> 02:11:10,892
Of course I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.

1677
02:11:11,539 --> 02:11:13,481
Not for an old crook like me.

1678
02:11:13,683 --> 02:11:15,625
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1679
02:11:19,154 --> 02:11:23,693
I find I'm so excited I can barely
sit still or hold a thought in my head.

1680
02:11:24,114 --> 02:11:27,310
I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.

1681
02:11:27,506 --> 02:11:29,895
A free man at the start
of a long journey...

1682
02:11:30,098 --> 02:11:32,585
...whose conclusion is uncertain.

1683
02:11:35,473 --> 02:11:38,026
I hope I can make it across the border.

1684
02:11:39,473 --> 02:11:42,375
I hope to see my friend
and shake his hand.

1685
02:11:44,176 --> 02:11:48,071
I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.

1686
02:11:49,840 --> 02:11:50,985
I hope.



0
